<p>&nbsp;<span style="font-size: large;">what is TERMUX ?</span></p><p></p><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEj5zT0awOSrpaPITTnR2nXlBVImgCu2OON1amWECdFVPXxxUuzUAAAM85yQ1jf4LzpBVKC-u7yrCGnABhPQMnBjAUyebDfJLVs-qC2WE4bXKcoeBRUkAGNwcx_DMx4hQHEByDWlIYmPEUKdtjrlQdmwp-mV_AQ3zNOgauU4P9QLsQnTjqssIWTL9rk1kg=s512" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" data-original-height="250" data-original-width="512" height="156" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEj5zT0awOSrpaPITTnR2nXlBVImgCu2OON1amWECdFVPXxxUuzUAAAM85yQ1jf4LzpBVKC-u7yrCGnABhPQMnBjAUyebDfJLVs-qC2WE4bXKcoeBRUkAGNwcx_DMx4hQHEByDWlIYmPEUKdtjrlQdmwp-mV_AQ3zNOgauU4P9QLsQnTjqssIWTL9rk1kg=w437-h156" width="437" /></a></div><br /><span style="font-size: large;"><br /></span><p></p><p><b style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Termux</b><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;</span><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">is a&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Terminal_emulator" style="background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: #0645ad; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-decoration-line: none;" title="Terminal emulator">terminal emulator</a><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;for&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Android_(operating_system)" style="background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: #0645ad; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-decoration-line: none;" title="Android (operating system)">Android</a><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;that allows for running a&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Linux" style="background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: #0645ad; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-decoration-line: none;" title="Linux">Linux</a><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;environment on an android device. In addition, various Linux software can be installed through the application's package manager.</span></p><p><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Termux installs a minimal base system automatically, additional packages are available using a package manager</span></p><p><span style="color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;"><span style="background-color: white;">FEATURES</span></span></p><p><span style="color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;"></span></p><div class="separator" style="clear: both; text-align: center;"><span style="color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;"><a href="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEif5iNX3z2sKNkDppAHqpIBoZZsNlaAFCK5Bl0Qi0r0BcB35oNmtJYi8jDrLf7rjrphBcyIA2ayeA6HHxxgGHSJX1aJ_8-3rRU8mIziHp2F4JB-TzfFO69BzpeUTEqReY3wcTHor0_j5tNFougVhUANWT-xWjpp-qwb9lv1ym0pmZekwub4lYV9bL3sBg=s1200" imageanchor="1" style="margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;"><img border="0" data-original-height="712" data-original-width="1200" height="190" src="https://blogger.googleusercontent.com/img/a/AVvXsEif5iNX3z2sKNkDppAHqpIBoZZsNlaAFCK5Bl0Qi0r0BcB35oNmtJYi8jDrLf7rjrphBcyIA2ayeA6HHxxgGHSJX1aJ_8-3rRU8mIziHp2F4JB-TzfFO69BzpeUTEqReY3wcTHor0_j5tNFougVhUANWT-xWjpp-qwb9lv1ym0pmZekwub4lYV9bL3sBg=w379-h190" width="379" /></a></span></div><span style="color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: medium;"><br /><span style="background-color: white;"><br /></span></span><p></p><p><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">Packages are cross-compiled with Android NDK and only have compatibility patches to get them working on Android. Since all files are installed at the application directory, rooting is not required</span></p><p><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">There are more than one thousand packages that can be downloaded and users can submit requests for new ones. Alternatively, they can be compiled from source as termux supports a variety of build tools including CMAKE</span><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;as well as compilers for&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C%2B%2B" style="background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: #0645ad; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-decoration-line: none;" title="C++">C++</a><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">,&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rust_(programming_language)" style="background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: #0645ad; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-decoration-line: none;" title="Rust (programming language)">Rust</a><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">,&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Go_(programming_language)" style="background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); color: #0645ad; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-decoration-line: none;" title="Go (programming language)">Go</a><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">&nbsp;and several others. Termux can also install Interpreters for languages like&nbsp;</span><span style="color: red;"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ruby_(programming_language)" style="background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-decoration-line: none;" title="Ruby (programming language)">Ruby</a><span style="background-color: white; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">,&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Python_(programming_language)" style="background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-decoration-line: none;" title="Python (programming language)">Python</a><span style="background-color: white; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">,&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/JavaScript" style="background: none rgb(255, 255, 255); font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; text-decoration-line: none;" title="JavaScript">JavaScript</a></span><span style="background-color: white; color: #202122; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px;">, etc.</span></p><h2 style="background-color: white; border-bottom: 1px solid rgb(162, 169, 177); font-family: &quot;Linux Libertine&quot;, Georgia, Times, serif; font-weight: normal; line-height: 1.3; margin: 1em 0px 0.25em; overflow: hidden; padding: 0px;"><span class="mw-headline" id="Package_management_and_distribution">Package management and distribution</span></h2><div><span class="mw-headline"><p style="background-color: white; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0.5em 0px;"><span style="color: #202122;">Packages in Termux are installed through the application's package manager (pkg) in the&nbsp;</span><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Deb_(file_format)" style="background: none; color: #0645ad; text-decoration-line: none;" title="Deb (file format)">.</a>deb<span style="color: #202122;">&nbsp;format. Although Termux uses the .deb format, normal Debian packages cannot be installed as Termux is not&nbsp;</span><span style="color: red;">FHS</span><span style="color: #202122;">&nbsp;compliant.</span><span style="color: #202122;">&nbsp;Users can also build and submit packages.</span></p><p style="background-color: white; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0.5em 0px;"><span style="color: #202122;"><br /></span></p><p style="background-color: white; font-family: sans-serif; font-size: 14px; margin: 0.5em 0px;"><span style="color: #202122;"><br /></span></p></span></div>
